'''Martin Thwait''' is a rogue who can be found inside the [[Rogues' Den]], located in [[Burthorpe]] by entering a trapdoor inside [[The Toad and Chicken]] inn. He sells a variety of [[Thieving]]-related items, like [[lockpick]]s for chests, [[stethoscope]]s for the local vaults, and an assortment of [[claws]].

If a player has achieved 99 Thieving, they can purchase a [[Thieving cape]] and its respective [[Thieving hood|hood]] from him for 99,000 coins. To access his [[Martin Thwait's Lost and Found|store]], players must have a level of 50 or higher in both the Thieving and [[Agility]] skills, or have a Thieving level of 99. Boosts cannot be used to fulfill either of these requirements.

==Treasure Trails==
{{Anagram|Martin Thwait|hard|RAT MAT WITHIN}}. The answer to his challenge: ''How many natural fires burn in Rogue's Den?'' is ''2''.

